        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Actually ravanta,</P><P>The mana conservation one is rather nice.  Saving 20percent on dots adds up over time.  Granted if you're looking at it on a per cast or within a per 10minute window, of course the effect is going to be negligable.  However over teh course of an hour or lets say 3+ hours of gameplay, its effect is substantial.</P><P>People pay tons of PP for those FT3 boots (myself included).  I havent done the math, but saving 90 mana per FP cast, if cast lets say once every 3 minutes while soloing really adds up fast.</P><P>I think its rather comical and ironic that our affliction items help us solo more than anything else. Necro's have been crying for group and raid enhancements for how long? In addition, vi has been nerfing our soloing abilities since the pre-kunark era.  Enhancing dot dps would have been great for raids. Why VI wont do this via crits and focus items, puzzles me.</P><P><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=55675" target="_blank">Tencor Laureate - 60th Warlock</a><br><BR><a href="http://www.veilofsilence.org" target="_blank">Veil of Silence</a><br> <BR>Innoruuk Server<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
